title.narrative: Biodiversity and Watersheds Improved for Strong Economy and Ecosystem Resilience (B+WISER)

description.narrative: (Philippines): B+WISER will continue to assist the Philippine Department of Environment and Natural Resources (DENR) at both the national and local levels to address threats to biodiversity and forest degradation, which will help slow, halt, or reverse greenhouse gas emissions. FY 2017 biodiversity funds will further institutionalize the Lawin (Philippine hawk eagle) biodiversity and forest protection system. This technology-based system enables the Philippine government to generate data for forest cover analysis, forest conservation area planning, and patrol planning and implementation. B+WISER will build the capacity of DENR on natural forest protection and forest management. Conservation financing schemes with the private sector will be implemented in select high conservation value Areas. FY 2017 Sustainable Landscapes funds will finance restoration initiatives for specific ecosystem services and the use of the Lawin system in areas with high rates of deforestation.
